es the fields of patient history and gender history. Based on the detailed examination of over fifty firsthand accounts, this fascinating volume offers unprecedented insight into what it was like to live, suffer, and inhabit a body more than three centuries ago.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDiseasesxHistoryx17th centuryxEngland. 0aDiseaseszEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 0aDiseaseszEnglandxHistoryy18th century. 0aPublic healthxHistoryx17th centuryxEngland. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300213478.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles